subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. Entirely black, sometimes with a very slight red tinge, dorsal surface completely asetose; frons flat with shallow postclypeal impression; pronotum moderately convex with indistinct lateroposterior depressions, lateral margins slightly angulate; elytra 1.15–1.20 times as long as wide, lateral margins slightly emarginate, posterior margin obliquely truncate; aedeagus slender, subcylindrical (
Fig. 71
).
